# Fix GitHub CI Errors

When the user asks to fix CI errors, follow these steps:

## 1. Check recent runs

```bash
gh run list --limit 5
```

## 2. Get failure details

```bash
gh run view <run_id> --log-failed
```

## 3. Fix the issue

- Read the failing file before editing
- Make the minimal fix
- Run the same check locally if possible (e.g. `pnpm run lint`, `pnpm test`)

## 4. Push the fix

```bash
git add <files> && git commit -m "<description of fix>" && git push origin main
```

## 5. Verify

Wait ~60s, then confirm the new CI run passes:

```bash
gh run list --limit 3
```

If still failing, repeat from step 2.
